bio: IKEA is a Swedish furniture giant founded in 1943 by Ingvar Kamprad. With a mission to make modern living affordable and accessible, IKEA has become one of the world's largest retailers of flat-pack furniture. From its humble beginnings as a small mail-order business to today's global presence with over 400 stores across more than 50 countries, IKEA has remained committed to innovative design, sustainability, and customer-centricity.
